                </TransformGroup>
            </TextBlock.RenderTransform><Run Text="&#x9;CIVIC - is a game about the evolution of settlement life. In this game, the user does not need to perform any actions, you just need to set the parameters and watch what is happening on the screen"/><Run Text=". "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="&#x9;S"/><Run Text="o, in the game there can be from one to six teams with unique colors (Red, Blue, Green, Orange, DarkOrange, Violet), which should be set"/><Run Text=" before"/><Run Text=" "/><Run Text="the start of the game."/><LineBreak/><Run Text="&#x9;Each team generates settlers who find a suitable place (there should be no other settlers and cities nearby) and build a city. "/><Run Text="Every &quot;year&quot; (every 3 seconds)"/><Run Text=" new people will come to each city"/><Run Text=", new settlers will appear and build new cities. If 3 cities are close to each other, then they are combined into a commune (in each commune, cities grow faster depending on the number of cities"/><Run Text=" in it"/><Run Text=")"/><LineBreak/><Run Text="&#x9;Different teams can declare war on each other. If the team is at war and it does not have a commune, then each city will allocate 10% of the population for units to fight"/><Run Text=". If there is at least one commune, then only units will be taken from the communes (the same 10% from each city, "/><Run Text="just"/><Run Text=" united into one unit)"/><Run Text=". If the team has no cities or settlers left, then the team loses and is destroyed"/><Run Text="."/><LineBreak/><Run Language="ru-ru" Text="&#x9;The "/><Run Text="&quot;"/><Run Language="ru-ru" Text="year"/><Run Text="&quot;"/><Run Language="ru-ru" Text=" and history of the main events in the game is recorded in the log on the left"/><Run Text=". Also available functions that allow to disable wars, speed up the game, pause, remove the"/><Run Language="ru-ru" Text=" "/><Run Text="log."/><LineBreak/><Run/></TextBlock>
